abstract: Former New York Mayor Mike Bloomberg has plunged over $400 million of his personal fortune into his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination, an astronomical sum that has led many of his rivals to charge that he is trying to buy the crown.
snippet: Former New York Mayor Mike Bloomberg has plunged over $400 million of his personal fortune into his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination, an astronomical sum that has led many of his rivals to charge that he is trying to buy the cro...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former New York Mayor Mike Bloomberg has plunged over $400 million of his personal fortune into his campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination, an astronomical sum that has led many of his rivals to charge that he is trying to buy the crown.

abstract: Readers critique how the candidates performed at a feisty debate that one termed a “disheartening spectacle of bombast, braggadocio and rude behavior.”

abstract: Three months after Bloomberg News tried to thread the needle with a plan for covering a presidential campaign with company founder Mike Bloomberg as a candidate, its journalists are learning how hard that can be.
snippet: Three months after Bloomberg News tried to thread the needle with a plan for covering a presidential campaign with company founder Mike Bloomberg as a candidate, its journalists are learning how hard that can be.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Three months after Bloomberg News tried to thread the needle with a plan for covering a presidential campaign with company founder Mike Bloomberg as a candidate, its journalists are learning how hard that can be.
headline_main: Bloomberg News Wrestles With Coverage of Candidate Bloomberg
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg News Wrestles With Coverage of Candidate Bloomberg

abstract: Morgan Stanley's takeover of brokerage E*Trade Financial Corp  reflects a more relaxed regulatory mood in Washington, but it is still a gamble in an election year that will see Democrats continue to shine a spotlight on Wall Street excesses, said analysts.
snippet: Morgan Stanley's takeover of brokerage E*Trade Financial Corp  reflects a more relaxed regulatory mood in Washington, but it is still a gamble in an election year that will see Democrats continue to shine a spotlight on Wall Street excesses, said ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Morgan Stanley's takeover of brokerage E*Trade Financial Corp  reflects a more relaxed regulatory mood in Washington, but it is still a gamble in an election year that will see Democrats continue to shine a spotlight on Wall Street excesses, said analysts.
headline_main: Morgan Stanley's E*Trade Deal to Test Washington's Regulatory Mood in Election Year
headline_print_headline: Morgan Stanley's E*Trade Deal to Test Washington's Regulatory Mood in Election Year

abstract: With the addition of Michael Bloomberg, the forum on NBC and MSNBC drew nearly 20 million viewers, beating the Golden Globes and Grammys.
snippet: With the addition of Michael Bloomberg, the forum on NBC and MSNBC drew nearly 20 million viewers, beating the Golden Globes and Grammys.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic presidential candidates smashed a ratings record on Wednesday night, drawing a combined audience of 19.7 million to the latest primary debate, Nielsen said on Thursday.

headline_print_headline: Las Vegas Primary Clash Sets a TV Ratings Record

abstract: She laced into Michael Bloomberg in a bid to invigorate her campaign, and then had her biggest 24 hours of fund-raising yet.
snippet: She laced into Michael Bloomberg in a bid to invigorate her campaign, and then had her biggest 24 hours of fund-raising yet.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Hours before Senator Elizabeth Warren would take the stage in front of the largest television audience in Democratic debate history, she was holed up in a Bellagio hotel suite outfitted with six podiums for her final practice session.

abstract: Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, facing increasing pressure to slow the Vermont senator’s rise before Super Tuesday, criticized his record on gun control and his chances against President Trump.
snippet: Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, facing increasing pressure to slow the Vermont senator’s rise before Super Tuesday, criticized his record on gun control and his chances against President Trump.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The day after a Democratic presidential debate brought out the candidates’ outrage at Michael R. Bloomberg, the focus turned back toward Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, who leads polls of Nevada, California and the nation.
